      "name": "Trojanized npm Package Supply Chain Compromise",
      "description": "Compromised maintainer accounts are used to publish trojanized versions of legitimate npm packages. These packages execute credential theft and exfiltration code during the installation process, specifically in the preinstall phase using lifecycle scripts.",
